00:32:03.096 --> 00:32:07.843
a good friend of mine,
and I love his book,

00:32:07.843 --> 00:32:13.730
and I love his wonderful
intuition about when the cart is

00:32:13.730 --> 00:32:16.150
going off the track.
 

00:32:16.150 --> 00:32:19.785
He tends to be right so it's
hard to deny that irrational

00:32:19.785 --> 00:32:23.420
exuberance is behind a lot of
the big messes we're in.

00:32:23.420 --> 00:32:27.673
However, as an economist,
you sort of want to see how

00:32:27.673 --> 00:32:31.598
much you can get with the
rational stories first,

00:32:31.598 --> 00:32:35.690
and then have the remainder be
the exuberance.

00:32:35.690 --> 00:32:37.210
We're going to push on that a
little bit--yeah.

00:32:37.210 --> 00:32:40.210
Student:  Yeah,
I interpret this chart as,

00:32:40.210 --> 00:32:43.280
if prices of asset values are
