00:33:55.170 --> 00:33:57.200
I want you to understand the
geography of this first.

00:33:57.200 --> 00:34:02.108
These are confidence bands and
if you're thinking--

00:34:02.108 --> 00:34:05.026
if you're a banker and you're
going to make a loan the first

00:34:05.026 --> 00:34:08.730
thing you want to know is,
is this loan to value ratio

00:34:08.730 --> 00:34:13.440
going to change a lot over the
time period of the loan?

00:34:13.440 --> 00:34:16.639
A lot of subprime loans sort of
reset after three years and so

00:34:16.639 --> 00:34:17.059
forth.
 

00:34:17.059 --> 00:34:19.449
You'd like to have some
confidence,

00:34:19.449 --> 00:34:22.760
or at least know how far down
the value could go,

00:34:22.760 --> 00:34:26.579
so that you--because you're
